						<p style="font-size:18px;line-height:25px;color:#000000; font-weight: 400; font-family: 'Roboto', Arial, sans-serif; margin:10px 0 20px;">It is possible to do some self-study with the Triage - ETEK booklet (attached). &nbsp;Then you can book in an online exam here: <a href="https://www.nursecpdonline.com.au/service/triage-skills-an-introduction-nurse-online-cpd-training/">Nurse CPD Online – Introduction to Triage</a>. This course costs approximately $35.00.<br />
						<br />
						Other options:<br />
						<br />
						FLECC (First Line Emergency Care Course) – NSW Health course<br />
						<br />
						WACHS Triage – WA Health course<br />
						<br />
						CRANA – "Triage Emergency Care" has theory &amp; practical components. 1 day face-to-face workshop.<br />
						You would need to register your interest via <a href="https://crana.org.au/learning-opportunities/courses/triage-emergency-care-online">CRANA’s website</a> for any upcoming courses that may become available.<br />
						<br />
						PLEASE NOTE: These courses are suggestions only, it is always best to also do your own research.</p>

